aware that it comes from the perspective of a novice programmer ...

I don't know what kind of people you were aiming for in LOVELACE, but I 
think it does an outstanding job of nurturing the interest of someone 
who is truly interested in Ada 95.  I noticed that you described it as 
a whirlwind tour.  I think that is true, but it was a whirlwind tour 
with many opportunities for brief reflection and with directions for 
detailed inquiries.  Specifically, I think that the quizzes with comments 
for both the right and the wrong answers really helps a novice, like me, 
to get some sense of progress.  Of course, more can be learned by working 
