David,

On page 12.4 of the Lovelace tutorial
(http://www.adahome.com/Tutorials/Lovelace/s12-4.htm),
you have the following fragment:

----

  type Tree_Node; -- Incomplete type declaration.
  type Tree_Access is access Tree_Node;
  type Tree_Node is
    record
      Parent      : Tree_Access;
      Left, Right : Tree_Access;
      Data        : Unbounded_String;
    end record;

Here's an example of statements using this tree data structure, if A and
B are of type Tree_Access: 

  A := new List_Node;
  B := new List_Node;
  A.Data := To_Unbounded_String("Hello!");   -- assign some data
  B.Data := To_Unbounded_String("Goodbye!");
  A.Left := B;                               -- connect them.
  B.Parent := A;

----

Note the incorrect statements

  A := new List_Node;
  B := new List_Node;

which should be

  A := new Tree_Node;
  B := new Tree_Node;


